Events.Text: <i>We didn't end up getting anything too fancy,░ neither of us had the stomach for anything too rich after the late night and we ended up in a small diner that did nice enough omelets.░ It was good to just to chill with Lex, and the diner was thankfully a quiet as we nursed our hangovers with black coffee and crisped bacon.

Events.Text: <i>After a little while I could feel the food coma starting to out-perform the coffee and decided that I was probably tired enough to pass out without Coby giving me another grilling about spending all that time with Lex.

Events.Text: <i>I dropped the husky back at their apartment building with a fond farewell.░ I went in for a hand shake,░ figuring anything more was pushing my luck,░ and they gave a high five then a fist pound in a cool fluid motion.░ I guess I should've figured the slap and dap was more Lex's style than a stuffy handshake or a hug.

Events.Text: <i>By the time I got home,░ Coby was deeply embroiled in one of his video games in the living room and I was able to sneak upstairs without the squawking inquisition.

'Days' maybe?░ When I'm rested up,░ I should get in contact about another adventure:░ Lex promised that the next one wouldn't just be drinking at a bar.

Events.Text: <i>Sinking into my pillow,░ I couldn't help the smile that played on my face at the scent of Lex's deodorant and the hint of aged tobacco leaves left hiding for me between the creases in the fabric.░ I wonder what other adventures Lex has in store for me...

Events.Text: <i>This was my first time in Lex's car,░ it was a pretty nice model,░ not a fancy sports car but it seemed well-loved:░ it certainly put my own car to shame with the empty water bottles and receipts cluttered around the front seats.░ The car was well-maintained despite that they'd mentioned owning it for years.

Events.Text: <i>There was a slight woody smell of warm tobacco, maybe even cigars,░ that made me think of my grandparents' house.░ Lex played disk jockey from a media player hooked into the sound system.

Events.Text: <i>Lex didn't seem like they'd beefed up the sound system much, at first,░ though considering the age of the car the USB connected hardware and the clarity of the guitars that came through the speakers proved otherwise,░ definitely better than the tinny-sounding ones that struggled to play along in my own car.

Events.Text: <i>Despite what I thought with the sporty car model and the torn pants,░ Lex was a pretty safe driver,░ almost cautious,░ and took each turn with impressive precision on the push and pull of the wheel,░ never crossing their hands or letting go the way my dad would terrify me with.

Events.Text: <i>We had Lex's car to ourselves,░ I suppose we'd be meeting their friends out wherever we were going.░ We weren't heading into the city, that was for sure,░ as we hit the main route out into the suburbs away from the coast.

Events.Text: <i>Crossing back over the road where the buildings were sparser,░ the first order of business was a quick off-road ramble.░ The light of the moon above made it easy enough to see and,░ traipsing through the trees a little a way,░ I finally got a good look at the abandoned building.

Events.Text: <i>It was sitting alone beyond a narrow clearing that might once have been a corporate maintained break area,░ judging by a couple of wooden picnic tables that had rotted through to mush.░ The building itself loomed over a small lot of cracked asphalt that the moss and grasses were doing their best to reclaim.░
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>It looked like the majority of the building was a squat two-story warehouse with an office building attached on one side.░ The structure was starting to look a little mossy, and the company name was all but sun-bleached out of existence░ (TomTech maybe?░ KernTech?)░ Our target waited for us,░ an ominous monolith above the trees.

Events.Text:
<i>But before that,░ the sound of voices and glow of flashlights between us and the building suggested that Lex's friends were waiting for us.░
Beyond an overgrown,░ prickly bush,░ three figures caught sight of us and waved us over with a quiet cheer.

Events.Text:
<i>The group were a little eclectic,░ but I expected that from Lex's punk-ish style of dress and music,░ Lex did say that their friends got them out of their shell a little more.░
The three had started the party early beers in hand.░ I guess,░ when you're planning to sneak around a building without permission,░ drinking in public is the least of their worries.

Events.Text: <i>We climbed through and,░ sliding the frosted glass window back closed,░ were immediately left to the use of our torches.░ It was surprising how dark it was as we migrated out into the old hallway.░ I suppose living in the city you get used to the street lights or even the ambient light of the buildings catching on the clouds.░ There wasn't even star light in here,░ it was a black hole...

Events.Text: <i>The office area seemed to be a simple square of hallways as we moved through;░ I was reminded of the Scooty Doo team from the cartoons,░ the five of us bunched up clutching our flashlights,░ exploring the dilapidated building.░ Maybe a police force was a better example,░ looking up at the nest of spiders where a ceiling tile had fallen down,░ checking each open door as we passed the eerily abandoned rooms.

Events.Text: <i>There were some scars of vandalism down the hall,░ someone had run along with a blunt object,░ maybe a pipe,░ scoring the walls,░ and some of the rooms looked like people might have crashed there for a night or lit small fires,░ but Kazee had ensured us that the dust on the desk top by the window meant that no one had been here for a while.░ Otherwise we wouldn't have entered.

Events.Text: <i>The warehouse seemed like it was used for packing,░ judging by the ancient shreds of boxes and plastic and an industrial shrink wrap machine that seemed to be rusted to the floor at the center of a spreading coppery stain.░ The back wall of the warehouse was partially circled by an ancient roller conveyor for parcels that lead to a large set of shutters,░ my guess was that they did a lot of shipping.
